The shape of teeth on the mandibles of 

Ocypus denticulminis


sp. nov.

shows some interesting variations. Specimens have been seen with both teeth that can be easily distinguished from each other (
Fig. 2-3 A
), with both teeth combined to form a knife-shaped structure (
Fig. 2-3 C
) and many transitions between these two forms (
